{
  "texts": [
    "Typically, these examples are assumed to be independent and identically distributed (i.i.d.) according to some unknown probability measure P on X × Y (with mass or density function p).",
    "The measure P characterizes the data-generating process and is the target of generative learning.",
    "While the latter is interested in the joint occurrence of data (X, Y), discriminative learning focuses on the conditional dependence of Y on X.",
    "It proceeds from a hypothesis space H ⊂ Y X, where each hypothesis is a map (predictor) X -→ Y.",
    "The learner then seeks the \"best predictor\", viz."
  ]
}